## Lookup arguments

Specify exactly one of:

| argument | behavior |
|---|---|
| `id` | Direct lookup by integer ID. |
| `name` | Exact-match lookup by name (fuzzy server search, then exact `name ==` filter). Names are unique server-side. Errors if zero or more than one provider matches. |

## Returned values

| attribute | description |
|---|---|
| `id` | Auth provider integer ID. |
| `name` | Provider name. |
| `provider_type` | One of `LDAP`, `OIDC`, `SAML` (see the table below). |
| `is_enabled` | Whether the provider is enabled. |
| `display_order` | Login-page display order (`>= 0`). |
| `config` | Per-`provider_type` config JSON (sensitive). **Secret fields are masked as `****`** in this read — they cannot be recovered from the data source. |
| `group_mappings_count` | Number of attached group→role mappings. |
| `created_at` | Creation timestamp. |
| `updated_at` | Last update timestamp. |

### `provider_type` values

| provider_type | meaning |
|---|---|
| `LDAP` | LDAP / Active Directory directory provider. |
| `OIDC` | OpenID Connect provider. |
| `SAML` | SAML 2.0 identity provider. |

For the full per-`provider_type` shape of `config` (every field, which are
required/optional with defaults, and which are secret), see the
[`mistershell_auth_provider` resource](../resources/auth_provider.md) page.
